Iran 's Revolutionary Guards ` harassed ' a US-flagged commercial ship just days before it seized a vessel carrying cargo and 34 sailors .
The two incidents have raised concerns about the security of shipping lanes in the strategic Strait of Hormuz .
The Iranian guards seized MV Maersk Tigris this week , by firing warning shots across the vessel 's bows .
Iran has said it seized control of the container ship due to a legal order following a dispute .